@startuml AdminSec_UC02-10_Gerer_Personnel
title UC-02-10: Gerer Personnel - AdminSecretariat (Tous Scenarios)

actor AdminSecretariat as A
participant Dashboard
participant Systeme
participant DB
participant Logs

A -> Dashboard: 1. Accede a Gestion Personnel
activate Dashboard

Dashboard -> DB: 2. Recupere tous consultants du secretariat (filtrer par secretariat_id)
activate DB

alt Erreur BD
  DB --> Dashboard: ERREUR: BD indisponible
  deactivate DB
  Dashboard --> A: ERREUR 500: Impossible charger personnel
  deactivate Dashboard
else BD disponible
  DB --> Dashboard: Retourne consultants (email, role, statut, dernier login)
  deactivate DB

  Dashboard --> A: 3. Affiche tableau consultants avec filtres
  deactivate Dashboard

  A -> Dashboard: 4. Clique pour ajouter consultant
  activate Dashboard

  Dashboard --> A: 5. Affiche formulaire ajout consultant
  deactivate Dashboard

  A -> Dashboard: 6. Saisit email et clique Creer
  activate Dashboard

  Dashboard -> Systeme: 7. Valide email format et unicite
  activate Systeme

  Systeme -> DB: 8. Verifie email non existe dans systeme
  activate DB

  alt Email invalide ou deja existe
    DB --> Systeme: ERREUR: Email existe ou format invalide
    deactivate DB
    Systeme --> Dashboard: ERREUR 400: Email invalide ou existe deja
    deactivate Systeme
    Dashboard --> A: ERREUR: Email deja utilise ou format invalide
    deactivate Dashboard
  else Email valide et unique
    DB --> Systeme: Email unique OK
    deactivate DB

    Systeme --> Dashboard: Validation OK
    deactivate Systeme

    Dashboard -> DB: 9. Cree consultant avec role et secretariat_id
    activate DB

    alt Erreur creation
      DB --> Dashboard: ERREUR: Creation echouee
      deactivate DB
      Dashboard --> A: ERREUR: Impossible creer consultant
      deactivate Dashboard
    else Creation OK
      DB -> DB: 10. INSERT consultant (email, secretariat_id, role, statut ACTIF)

      DB -> DB: 11. Genere mot de passe temporaire (hash)

      DB --> Dashboard: Consultant cree
      deactivate DB

      Dashboard -> DB: 12. Enregistre log audit: Ajout consultant (admin, email, timestamp, secretariat_id)
      activate DB
      DB --> Dashboard: Audit log enregistre en BD
      deactivate DB

      Dashboard -> Logs: 13. Log event: Consultant ajoute
      activate Logs
      Logs --> Dashboard: Event loggue pour monitoring
      deactivate Logs

      Dashboard --> A: 14. SUCCES! Consultant ajoute\nEmail invitation envoye
      deactivate Dashboard

      note over A, Logs
        **CONSULTANT AJOUTE OK:**
        - Consultant cree
        - Mot de passe genere
        - DB: Audit logs persistes
        - Logs: Events loggues
      end note
    end
  end

  A -> Dashboard: 15. Clique sur consultant existant
  activate Dashboard

  Dashboard -> DB: 16. Recupere details consultant (verifier secretariat_id)
  activate DB

  alt Consultant inexistant OU n'appartient pas au secretariat
    DB --> Dashboard: ERREUR 404 ou 403: Non trouve ou acces refuse
    deactivate DB
    Dashboard --> A: ERREUR: Consultant inexistant ou acces refuse
    deactivate Dashboard
  else Consultant existe
    DB --> Dashboard: Retourne infos completes (permissions, historique)
    deactivate DB

    Dashboard --> A: 17. Affiche fiche consultant
    deactivate Dashboard

    A -> Dashboard: 18. Clique Modifier Permissions
    activate Dashboard

    Dashboard --> A: 19. Affiche formulaire permissions
    deactivate Dashboard

    A -> Dashboard: 20. Change permissions et clique Sauvegarder
    activate Dashboard

    Dashboard -> Systeme: 21. Valide permissions (coherence avec role)
    activate Systeme

    alt Permissions invalides
      Systeme --> Dashboard: ERREUR: Permissions invalides
      deactivate Systeme
      Dashboard --> A: ERREUR: Permissions non acceptables
      deactivate Dashboard
    else Permissions valides
      deactivate Systeme

      Dashboard -> DB: 22. Met a jour permissions en transaction
      activate DB

      alt Transaction echouee
        DB --> Dashboard: ERREUR: Transaction echouee
        deactivate DB
        Dashboard --> A: ERREUR: Impossible modifier permissions
        deactivate Dashboard
      else Transaction OK
        DB -> DB: 23. UPDATE consultant permissions

        DB -> DB: 24. INSERT log modification (admin, ancien, nouveau, timestamp, secretariat_id)

        DB --> Dashboard: Permissions mises a jour
        deactivate DB

        Dashboard -> DB: 25. Enregistre log audit: Modification permissions (admin, consultant, timestamp, secretariat_id)
        activate DB
        DB --> Dashboard: Audit log enregistre en BD
        deactivate DB

        Dashboard -> Logs: 26. Log event: Permissions modifiees
        activate Logs
        Logs --> Dashboard: Event loggue pour monitoring
        deactivate Logs

        Dashboard --> A: 27. SUCCES! Permissions mises a jour
        deactivate Dashboard

        note over A, Logs
          **PERMISSIONS MISES A JOUR OK:**
          - Consultant: nouvelles permissions
          - DB: Audit logs persistes
          - Logs: Events loggues
        end note
      end
    end

    A -> Dashboard: 28. Clique Desactiver Consultant
    activate Dashboard

    Dashboard --> A: 29. Affiche confirmation avec implications
    deactivate Dashboard

    A -> Dashboard: 30. Confirme desactivation
    activate Dashboard

    Dashboard -> DB: 31. Marque consultant INACTIF
    activate DB

    DB -> DB: 32. Log desactivation (admin, timestamp, secretariat_id)

    DB --> Dashboard: Consultant desactif
    deactivate DB

    Dashboard -> DB: 33. Enregistre log audit: Desactivation consultant (admin, consultant, timestamp, secretariat_id)
    activate DB
    DB --> Dashboard: Audit log enregistre en BD
    deactivate DB

    Dashboard -> Logs: 34. Log event: Consultant desactive
    activate Logs
    Logs --> Dashboard: Event loggue pour monitoring
    deactivate Logs

    Dashboard --> A: 35. SUCCES! Consultant desactive\nNe peut plus se connecter
    deactivate Dashboard

    note over A, Logs
      **DESACTIVATION OK:**
      - Consultant marque INACTIF
      - Connexion bloquee
      - DB: Audit logs persistes
      - Logs: Events loggues
    end note
  end
end

@enduml
